From 13e7cc0475a2f3b4df61749b176d7ce72ab6ddfd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?K=C3=A9vin=20Remondi=C3=A8re?= <remondiere@openclaw.local>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 22:48:24 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] fix: MTP support for Qwen3.5-35B-A3B MoE (4 bugs)

1. TENSOR_SKIP: was unconditionally skipping MTP layer tensors even
   when mtp=true. Now checks !model.mtp before skipping.

2. cparams.mtp whitelist: was forced to 0 for all archs except
   GLM4_MOE. Added QWEN35MOE and QWEN35 to the whitelist.

3. Gated Q: build_mtp_tail used raw QKV matmul which doesn't handle
   Qwen3.5's gated attention (wq contains Q+Gate, 2x normal size).
   Replaced with build_std_attention which correctly splits Q/Gate.

4. M-RoPE: MTP attention was called with is_multi=false but Qwen3.5
   uses Multi-RoPE (rope_sections=[11,11,10]).

Graph now builds successfully. Remaining: compute buffer needs
reserve for MTP graph size (crashes during graph compute, not build).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
